To determine the likely amino acid sequence for some portion of the transmembrane domain of the protein ALPHA, we need to consider the properties of amino acids that are typically found in transmembrane regions. Transmembrane domains are usually composed of hydrophobic amino acids because they interact with the hydrophobic core of the lipid bilayer.
